  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Response in AP and Odisha post Cyclone Titli</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. 2000 most vulnerable HHs have access to essential hygiene materials leading and would have improved hygiene practices and good health.  
2. 2000 most vulnerable HHs will get household NFIs to meet their basic needs. 
3. 2000 most vulnerable HHs have received shelter NFIs including tarpaulins and ground sheets and have access to improved shelter.
4.To provide WASH kit/ NFI and clean drinking water to 1500 HH in Ganjam district of Odisha.
4 15,000 people are made aware of the good hygiene practices to protect themselves from diseases and demonstrate change in the knowledge and attitude towards good hygiene.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project we will support 2000 families with WASH and Shelter/NFI support also 10000 community people on hygiene awareness.  The partner will also work Gajapati district of Odisha in Mohanna&apos;s block 20 villages and to provide WASH hygiene kit and NFI to 1500 HH after the assessment process.</narrative>
  </description>
